  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT93-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">vāyilākap pukkat tōḻikku vāyiṉ maṟuttatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Mediation/the door refused to the confidante who had entered as a mediator.</p>
          </div>



        <div xml:id="KT93">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                naṉṉalan tolaiya nalamikac cāa</l>
<l>                yiṉṉuyir kaḻiyiṉu muraiya lavarnamak</l>
<l>                kaṉṉaiyu mattaṉu mallarō tōḻi</l>
<l>                pulaviyaḵ tevaṉō vaṉpilaṅ kaṭaiyē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
                <l rend="indent">Even if [our] dear life is passing,</l>
                <l rend="indent">since [our] innocence<note place="foot">Here again by another attribute, i.e. <term xml:lang="ta">nal</term> "good", <term xml:lang="ta">nalam</term> appears to be divided into two varieties, and presumably the distinguished kind refers again to her virginity (cf. <term xml:lang="ta">putu nalaṉ</term> KT 81).</note> is lost [and] beauty wasting away fast,</l>
                <l rend="indent3">don't speak:</l>
                <l>isn't he mother and father [to us], friend?</l>
                <l>Being vexed, what [is] that, [if his] love is not with us?</l>
                <lg type="alternate" sameAs="4b">
                  <l>What [is] the [good] of being vexed?</l>
                  <l>With us there is no love [for him anymore].</l>
                </lg>
                <lg type="alternate" sameAs="4c">
                    <l>What [is] the [good] of being vexed?</l>
                    <l>We are boundless in [our] love [for him].</l>
                </lg>
                
                        
                
                
                </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
